overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by adding database capabilities, an admin dashboard, and an
  authentication system. After evaluating the existing codebase, a plan was
  developed to update demographic data fields, create a Prisma model for
  questionnaire responses, implement API routes for data submission and
  retrieval (including CSV export), and build a simple admin dashboard. A key
  decision was to use NeonDB for the PostgreSQL database and a straightforward
  password-based authentication. During implementation, the authentication
  system was refactored to leverage Next.js middleware for cleaner route
  protection. The database was successfully set up, and comprehensive testing
  confirmed that all API endpoints, admin login/logout, and data handling
  functionalities were working correctly, despite an initial UI testing hiccup
  with form submission.
